> The week just isn't complete without a taco night. If you agree (and how could you not?), you're in luck! Our chefs put together a sweet and savory version that's sure to satisfy. There's saucy beef and charred bell pepper, plus a refreshing mango salsa and smoky red pepper crema, all piled into steamy-soft tortillas. It may be a weeknight, but these tacos will take your taste buds on an island vacation.

== Mango Salsa ==

Wash and dry produce. Drain @mango{4%ounce}. Finely dice @roma tomato{1}(finely diced).

Halve, peel, and thinly slice half the @red onion{1}(halved, peeled, and thinly sliced); mince a few slices until you have 1 TBSP. (For 4 servings, thinly slice whole onion; mince a few slices until you have 2 TBSP.) Zest and quarter @lime{1}(zested and quartered) (for 4, zest one lime and quarter both). Halve, core, and thinly slice @green bell pepper{1}(halved, cored, and thinly sliced) into strips.

In a #small bowl{}, combine mango, tomato, minced onion, lime zest, and juice from half the lime. Season with @salt{pinch}.

== Beef & Veggies ==

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add sliced onion, bell pepper, and a pinch of salt. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender and lightly charred, ~{5-7%minutes}. (TIP: Add a splash of water if veggies begin to brown too quickly.) Season with salt and @pepper{pinch}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add @ground beef{10%ounce}, @blackening spice{1%tablespoon}, and a big pinch of salt. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir in @beef stock concentrate{1}, @water{2%tablespoon} (3 TBSP for 4 servings); bring to a simmer.

Return veggies to pan and stir until thoroughly combined. (TIP: Add a splash or two of water, if necessary, until mixture is saucy.) Taste and season with salt and pepper.

== Assembly ==

Meanwhile, wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Divide tortillas between plates and fill with beef and veggie filling. Top with mango salsa and @smoky red pepper crema{4%tablespoon}. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.